'''Fabio Fabene''' (born 12 March 1959) has been the Under-Secretary of the [[Synod of Bishops (Catholic)|Synod of Bishops]] since his appointment on 8 February 2014 by [[Pope Francis]]. He was consecrated bishop on 30 May 2014.

==Biography==

===Early life===
Fabene studied at the minor seminary in the diocese of [[Montefiascone]]. He went on to complete his studies in theology at the Pontifical Regional Seminary in [[Viterbo]] and was [[Holy Orders|ordained]] a priest for the diocese of Montefiascone on 26 May 1984. He was sent to Rome where he earned a doctorate in Canon law (JCD) from the [[Pontifical Lateran University]].<ref>[http://press.vatican.va/content/salastampa/en/bollettino/pubblico/2014/04/08/0251/00558.html]</ref>

===Priesthood and career===
He did pastoral work in the diocese and was later appointed chancellor, serving from 1984 until 1998. After this appointment, he taught canon law. Since 1 January 1998 he entered the service of the [[Roman Curia]] serving in the [[Congregation for Bishops]] where he went on to become head of office in 2010.<ref>[http://press.vatican.va/content/salastampa/en/bollettino/pubblico/2014/04/08/0251/00558.html]</ref> Since 1996 he worked as a judge in the marriage tribunal of Lazio for Diocese of Rome.

